org.drools.planner.examples.ras2012.model

Class Route

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.drools.planner.examples.ras2012.Visualizable
      • org.drools.planner.examples.ras2012.model.Route
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<Route>, Directed

    public class Route
extends Visualizable
implements Comparable<Route>, Directed
    Represents a way in which it is possible to travel the Territory. When constructed using Route.Builder, it is assigned an ArcProgression, which is a huge cache of various information about it. Note: this class has a natural ordering that is inconsistent with equals.

      • isPossibleForTrain

        public boolean isPossibleForTrain(Train t)

        Whether or not a particular Train is allowed on the route.

        It would be forbidden, when the Train:

        • Goes the opposite direction than the route.
        • Is required to pass through Node that is not on this route.
        • Is longer than one of the sidings on this route. (Required by RAS problem description.)
        • Carries hazardous materials and the route contains sidings. (Required by RAS problem description.)
        • Is heavy and the route contains sidings. Although technically not required by the RAS problem description, this is the easiest way to fulfill the requirement of never sending heavy Train to sidings when meet-passing another Train.
        Parameters:
        t - The train in question.
        Returns:
        True if this route is possible for the Train. The results are cached.
